text: I was chatting about Win10 with a friend yesterday evening, and he pointed out that the numbers 4 and 9 are considered unlucky in Japanese culture because their pronunciations are similar to the words for "kill/death" (4) and "suffering" (9). Perhaps someone at Microsoft wanted to avoid associating their flagship OS with the idea of suffering. :scream:
